{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place butter, shallots and garlic in mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then sauté <b>3 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>.","Add water, stock paste and 1 tsp of the peppercorns to mixing bowl. Insert simmering basket, then weigh potatoes into it and cook <b>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Meanwhile, place a large frying pan over high heat and season lamb with salt and pepper. Once pan is hot, sear lamb on both sides (approx. 1-2 minutes each side) until lightly browned.","Transfer seared lamb to Varoma dish and Varoma tray, then set Varoma aside. Place 1 tbsp water in hot frying pan and stir over heat to de-glaze the pan. Turn off heat and allow pan to cool.","Arrange asparagus and carrot around seared lamb in Varoma dish and on Varoma tray, then place Varoma into position and cook <b>4 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Lamb will be cooked medium-rare. If desired, continue cooking until lamb, asparagus, carrots and potatoes are cooked to your preference.","Transfer lamb, asparagus, carrots and potatoes to a large serving bowl and cover to rest and keep warm. The lamb will continue to cook as it rests. Retain stock in mixing bowl.","In a ceramic or glass bowl, combine whisky and cornflour together, then set aside.","Add remaining 1 tsp peppercorns, cream, reserved pan juices and reserved whisky and cornflour mixture to stock in mixing bowl and reduce <b>10-12 min\/90°C\/\/speed <b>, <strong>without measuring cup.<\/strong> ","Slice lamb and serve with potatoes, carrots and asparagus, drizzled with pink peppercorn sauce."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["40 g butter, cut in pieces (1-2 cm)","2 banana shallots (approx. 30 g), peeled and cut in halves","2 garlic cloves","220 g water","½ tsp meat stock paste, to taste (see Tips)","2 tsp pink peppercorns","300 g new potatoes, unpeeled, washed and cut in pieces (2-3 cm)","400 - 500 g lamb loins, boneless (approx. 3-4 fillets)","1 pinch sea salt","1 pinch ground black pepper","1 Tbsp water, to de-glaze frying pan","1 bunch green asparagus (130-150 g), trimmed and cut in halves","1 carrot, cut in matchsticks","1 Tbsp whisky","1 tsp maize flour","60 g whipping cream"]}],"id":"r146835","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-8y10DMdeQQE\/XZQHa2nEqwI\/AAAAAAAAcII\/2kqFMuOzXEIWZcjS6pw4AvBV3_l8UEc0ACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_ix52CJEnAy13fjkj.png","title":"Lamb Fillets with Pink Peppercorn Sauce","publishedAt":"2017-09-04T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"29 g","fat":"29.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"12.8 g","calories":"1830 kJ \/ 435 kcal"},"usefulItems":"frying pan, large serving bowl, hob","hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> for the meat stock paste recipe."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","30m","4 portions"]}